{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ff8d1dce-52d9-4980-89d5-9f801d1f4cb5","content":"Here's the mapping. First, add these NuGet packages to your test project(s):\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\nEnable the platform bridge in your test project or `Directory.Build.props`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThen your new command becomes:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Switch-by-switch mapping:**\n\n| VSTest (old) | Microsoft.Testing.Platform (new) |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter` | `--filter` (stays before `--`) |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\nEverything after `--` is forwarded to the Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner; everything before it is handled by `dotnet test` itself.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c3f26a3b-6366-46f9-8e0c-5712022be987","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a `dotnet test` command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure - I don't need to search the codebase for this.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences:\n- `--filter` → `--filter`(same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nNow I need to clarify how the runner is actually invoked. With .NET 9 SDK, `dotnet test` uses the new platform natively, but on .NET 8, the approach depends on your project configuration - you might need to use `dotnet run` or invoke the executable directly unless the project is explicitly configured to use the new test runner.\n\nOn .NET 8, you can still use `dotnet test` if you add `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` to your project file, though the CLI arguments change significantly. For filtering, `--filter` works with `dotnet test`, but calling the test app directly uses `--treenode-filter` instead. The tricky part is that many legacy VSTest switches don't translate directly when using the new platform through `dotnet test` - the extensions need to be added to support them.\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you install extension packages for additional features like TRX reporting, code coverage, crash dumps, and hang dumps, each with their own command-line flags. When running the test executable directly, you can chain multiple options together to enable all these diagnostics at once.\n\nFor .NET 8 specifically, I need to ensure the project has `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` set so that `dotnet test` properly bridges to the platform and passes those extension options through correctly. I need to specify the required NuGet packages for the testing extensions and configure the project file to enable the Microsoft Testing Platform integration with `dotnet test`. The property name varies by .NET version—newer versions use `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform` while .NET 8 uses `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`—so I'll note that distinction for clarity.","outputTokens":1763,"requestId":"981C:32FC8B:180701:1F4195:69FFD845"},"id":"849d4e29-2c8d-4226-8e9e-6641e2d57fb4","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:59:14.036Z","parentId":"fb5448d8-8213-4dc2-acca-085094f641e2"}
